Detailed Description

Frame is a list of ordered closure.

The frame correspond to an activation frame associated to each evaluation of closure, i.e. a call to function. A frame stores the list of created closures using the order of creation. Each newly created closure is added into the back side of the list, while they are consumed in the front side (FIFO queue). Frames are order into a stack.

The initialization of the frame is not made by constructor or direct call to initialize method. For performance design purpose, frames are initialized when they are pushed into the stack. The same design has been choose for the initialization of closure objects.

Warning:
Any modification or extension of the Frame structure implies to modify Core::Stack::push
